---
import VisualPlate from '../components/VisualPlate.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Prompted Psyche, my research-informed project on AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI Interaction."
>
  <article class="lovable-page about-page">
    <header class="lovable-page-hero">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="lovable-heading-narrow">
          <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
          <h1>About Prompted Psyche</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Prompted Psyche is my project on the human side of artificial intelligence:
            essays, concepts, talks and consulting on how AI changes thought, trust,
            communication, creativity and work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="editorial-block">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">01</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Project</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>How I look at AI</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              I am interested not only in what AI can do, but in what happens to people
              when they start to use it: trust model outputs, delegate tasks, create
              with AI and communicate through AI-shaped systems.
            </p>
            <p>
              I connect the psychology of AI use with questions about communication,
              work, responsibility, creativity and culture.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-block with-side-note">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">02</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Interpretive lens</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Film, attention and AI</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              My background in film, editing and post-production shapes how I think
              about AI: through narrative, attention, image, emotion and the way
              technologies reorganize creative and communicative work.
            </p>
            <p>
              It gives me a way to read AI not only as a tool, but as something that
              changes attention, context, authorship and the conditions of communication.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="floating-note" aria-hidden="true">
        <span></span>
        Narrative, attention, image, emotion
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section" aria-labelledby="lenses-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="compact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">03</p>
          <h2 id="lenses-title">Three lenses</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="lovable-lens-grid">
          <article class="lens-item">
            <p>01</p>
            <h3>Trust and decisions</h3>
            <span>
              When does an AI output begin to feel credible? How does it shape
              judgment, verification and responsibility?
            </span>
          </article>
          <article class="lens-item lens-item-offset">
            <p>02</p>
            <h3>Communication and emotion</h3>
            <span>
              How do AI systems change language, validation, perceived understanding
              and the rhythm of interaction?
            </span>
          </article>
          <article class="lens-item">
            <p>03</p>
            <h3>Work and creativity</h3>
            <span>
              How does AI enter writing, research, decision-making, image-making and
              creative authorship?
            </span>
          </article>
        </div>

        <div class="quote-diagram">
          <blockquote>
            We prompt machines. Machines prompt us back.
          </blockquote>
          <div>
            <VisualPlate variant="attention-frame" class="about-attention-visual" caption="Human-AI attention field" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-block">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">04</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Research background</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Research background</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              I am developing registered research projects in progress on psychological
              and creative aspects of human-AI relations, including AI chatbot use,
              authorship, authenticity and creative control in AI-supported practice.
            </p>
            <p>
              This work is ongoing and forms part of the background of Prompted Psyche.
              Public essays and concepts are source-informed, but they should not be
              presented as finished peer-reviewed research.
            </p>
            <p class="orcid-row">
              <span>ORCID</span>
              <a href="https://orcid.org/0009-0001-0715-0517" rel="me noopener">
                0009-0001-0715-0517
              </a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-final-links">
      <div class="lovable-container final-link-grid">
        <a href="/concepts/">Explore concepts <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
        <a href="/consulting/">See consulting <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
